# ZephyrV2 - Advanced Educational Platform

ZephyrV2 is a comprehensive educational platform that combines AI-powered learning assistance, offline-capable note-taking, intelligent scheduling, and advanced study tools for high school and college students.

## ğŸš€ Key Features

### AI Learning Assistance
- Multi-specialized AI chatbots (General, Math/Physics, CS, Document Analysis)
- Real-time code analysis and compilation
- LaTeX equation rendering and solving
- Document analysis and summarization
- Video/audio lecture analysis with auto-timestamping

### Note-Taking System
- Rich text editing with Markdown support
- Offline-first architecture with sync
- Mathematical equation support
- Code blocks with syntax highlighting
- Voice recording and transcription
- Version control and history

### Study Tools
- AI-powered flashcard generation
- Intelligent test creation
- Interactive math/physics visualization
- Real-time collaboration
- Smart document organization
- Citation management

### Calendar & Planning
- AI-optimized scheduling
- Study time allocation
- Smart break reminders
- External calendar integration
- Workload balancing

## ğŸ›  Technology Stack

### Frontend
- **Web Application**
  - Next.js 14+ with TypeScript
  - Tailwind CSS
  - shadcn/ui components
  - WebAssembly (Rust)
  - Service Workers
  - IndexedDB & SQLite

- **Mobile Application**
  - React Native
  - SQLite
  - Background services
  - Push notifications

### Backend
- **API Gateway & Core Services**
  - Go (Fiber/Chi)
  - GORM
  - JWT authentication

- **Real-time Services**
  - Elixir (Phoenix)
  - WebSocket
  - PubSub system

- **Computation Services**
  - Rust (Actix-web)
  - WebAssembly
  - Math computation engine

- **Cache & State**
  - Gleam
  - Redis
  - Distributed state handling

### Database & Storage
- PostgreSQL (Primary Database)
- Redis (Cache Layer)
- S3/GCS (File Storage)
- CDN integration

## ğŸ”’ Security Features
- End-to-end encryption
- JWT-based authentication
- OAuth2 support
- MFA integration
- At-rest encryption
- Client-side encryption

## ğŸ“Š Monitoring & Analytics
- Prometheus metrics
- Grafana dashboards
- Error tracking
- Usage analytics
- A/B testing support

## ğŸš€ Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- Go 1.21+
- Rust
- Docker & Docker Compose
- PostgreSQL 15+
- Redis

### Development Setup
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/zephyr-v2.git

# Install dependencies
pnpm install

# Start development environment
docker-compose up -d
pnpm dev
```

